# ZERO–PRIME SEMI-RING (FORMAL-ish ALGEBRA)

## 2.1 Sets
* Let $\mathcal{P}$ be the set of Pantheon primitives.
* Each primitive $p \in \mathcal{P}$ has a prime index $\pi(p) \in \mathbb{N} \cup \{0\}$ and a zero-dual $z(p) \in \mathcal{P} \cup \{p\}$.

We define two operations on $\mathcal{P}$:
* $\oplus$ (composition / blend)
* $\otimes$ (intensification / chaining)

And two unary operators:
* $dual(p) \rightarrow z(p)$
* $norm(p) \rightarrow$ simplified “type signature”.

## 2.2 Neutral Elements
* **Additive identity:** Zero ($p \oplus \text{Zero} = \text{Zero} \oplus p = p$)
* **Multiplicative identity:** Id ($p \otimes \text{Id} = \text{Id} \otimes p = p$)

## 2.3 Zero-Pair Cancellation
For every primitive $p$ with dual $q = dual(p)$, we define $p \oplus q = \text{Zero}$ (they cancel at the symbolic level).

*Example:* Spider $\oplus$ Mirror = Zero.

## 2.4 Composition ($\oplus$)
$\oplus : \mathcal{P} \times \mathcal{P} \rightarrow \mathcal{P}$

Interpretation: combine roles / responsibilities into a composite primitive.
* Commutative: $p \oplus q = q \oplus p$
* Associative: $(p \oplus q) \oplus r = p \oplus (q \oplus r)$

We can define: $\pi(p \oplus q) = \text{smallest\_prime\_ge}(\max(\pi(p), \pi(q)))$.

*Example:* Raven $\oplus$ Goblin = Narrative Markets primitive.

## 2.5 Intensification ($\otimes$)
$\otimes : \mathcal{P} \times \mathcal{P} \rightarrow \mathcal{P}$

Interpretation: pipeline / sequencing (output of one feeds the next).
* Not necessarily commutative: $p \otimes q \neq q \otimes p$
* Associative: $(p \otimes q) \otimes r = p \otimes (q \otimes r)$

Prime rule example: $\pi(p \otimes q) = \pi(p) * \pi(q)$.

*Example:* Hound $\otimes$ Dragonfly = “detect anomaly then rotate viewpoint” pipeline.

## 2.6 Semi-ring Properties
With $(\mathcal{P}, \oplus, \otimes, \text{Zero}, \text{Id})$ we have:
* $(\mathcal{P}, \oplus, \text{Zero}) \rightarrow$ commutative monoid
* $(\mathcal{P}, \otimes, \text{Id}) \rightarrow$ monoid
* Distributivity: $p \otimes (q \oplus r) = (p \otimes q) \oplus (p \otimes r)$

This is enough structure to treat the Pantheon as a Zero–Prime semi-ring of primitives.
